data.value:
Sarangkot is Ward 18 of Pokhara, Kaski District, Nepal, after it was merged into the city in 2015. It is a popular tourist destination for those who arrive in Pokhara. At the 1991 Nepal census it had a total population of 5,060 with 1,010 individual households. Sarangkot located in Gandaki Zone is a renowned place for its awe-inspiring views of the Himalayan ranges and sunrise and sunset views. From here you can spot out spectacular views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna, and Manaslu. Especially for Annapurna ranges, this is the best place to witness.
In addition to the fantastic views of the village, many adventurous acts address the thrilling atmosphere for adrenaline rushers. Zip-lining, Paragliding, trekking, and hiking are the popular adventurous activities to take part. Notably, Zip-lining in Sarangkot is one of the best-ever in the world. Simply, Sarangkot is a destination blended with beauty and adventure.
District: Kaski District Zone: Gandaki Zone Area code: 061
